134 struct FunctionInfo {
135 std::string name;
136 uint64_t pc_begin = 0, pc_end = 0;
137 vector<LocalVariable> variables;
138 uint64_t def_loc = 0, spec_loc = 0;
139 // The stack variable offsets are w.r.t either:
140 // gcc: the top of the stack frame (one below the return address to the caller)
141 // clang with frame pointers: the bottom of the stack frame (one above the return address to this function)
142 // clang without frame pointers: the top of the stack frame (...TODO...)
143 enum { Unknown = 0,
144 GCC,
145 ClangFP,
146 ClangNoFP } frame_base;
147 FunctionInfo()
148 : name("") {
149 }
150
151 bool operator<(const FunctionInfo &other) const {
152 return pc_begin < other.pc_begin;
153 }
154 };

194 DebugSections(const std::string &binary)
195 : calibrated(false), working(false) {
196 std::string binary_path = binary;
197#ifdef __APPLE__
198 size_t last_slash = binary_path.rfind('/');
199 if (last_slash == std::string::npos ||
200 last_slash >= binary_path.size() - 1) {
201 last_slash = 0;
202 } else {
203 last_slash++;
204 }
205 std::string file_only = binary_path.substr(last_slash, binary_path.size() - last_slash);
206 binary_path += ".dSYM/Contents/Resources/DWARF/" + file_only;
207#endif

209 debug(5) << "Loading " << binary_path << "\n";
210
211 load_and_parse_object_file(binary_path);

214 int count_trailing_zeros(int64_t x) {
215 for (int i = 0; i < 64; i++) {
216 if (x & (1 << i)) {
217 return i;
218 }
219 }
220 return 64;
221 }

223 void calibrate_pc_offset(void (*fn)()) {
224 // Calibrate for the offset between the instruction pointers
225 // in the debug info and the instruction pointers in the
226 // actual file.
227 bool found = false;
228 uint64_t pc_real = (uint64_t)fn;
229 int64_t pc_adjust = 0;
230 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
231 if (functions[i].name == "HalideIntrospectionCanary::offset_marker" &&
232 functions[i].pc_begin) {
233
234 uint64_t pc_debug = functions[i].pc_begin;
235
236 if (calibrated) {
237 // If we're already calibrated, we should find a function with a matching pc
238 if (pc_debug == pc_real) {
239 return;
240 }
241 } else {
242 int64_t pc_adj = pc_real - pc_debug;
243
244 // Offset must be a multiple of 4096
245 if (pc_adj & (4095)) {
246 continue;
247 }
248
249 // If we find multiple matches, pick the one with more trailing zeros
250 if (!found ||
251 count_trailing_zeros(pc_adj) > count_trailing_zeros(pc_adjust)) {
252 pc_adjust = pc_adj;
253 found = true;
254 }
255 }
256 }
257 }
258
259 if (!found) {
260 if (!calibrated) {
261 debug(2) << "Failed to find HalideIntrospectionCanary::offset_marker\n";
262 } else {
263 debug(2) << "Failed to find HalideIntrospectionCanary::offset_marker at the expected location\n";
264 }
265 working = false;
266 return;
267 }
268
269 debug(5) << "Program counter adjustment between debug info and actual code: " << pc_adjust << "\n";
270
271 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
272 FunctionInfo &f = functions[i];
273 f.pc_begin += pc_adjust;
274 f.pc_end += pc_adjust;
275 for (size_t j = 0; j < f.variables.size(); j++) {
276 LocalVariable &v = f.variables[j];
277 for (size_t k = 0; k < v.live_ranges.size(); k++) {
278 v.live_ranges[k].pc_begin += pc_adjust;
279 v.live_ranges[k].pc_end += pc_adjust;
280 }
281 }
282 }
283
284 for (size_t i = 0; i < source_lines.size(); i++) {
285 source_lines[i].pc += pc_adjust;
286 }
287
288 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
289 global_variables[i].addr += pc_adjust;
290 }
291
292 calibrated = true;
293 }

295 int find_global_variable(const void *global_pointer) {
296 if (global_variables.empty()) {
297 debug(5) << "Considering possible global at " << global_pointer << " but global_variables is empty\n";
298 return -1;
299 }
300 debug(5) << "Considering possible global at " << global_pointer << "\n";
301
302 debug(5) << "Known globals range from " << std::hex << global_variables.front().addr << " to " << global_variables.back().addr << std::dec << "\n";
303 uint64_t address = (uint64_t)(global_pointer);
304 size_t hi = global_variables.size();
305 size_t lo = 0;
306 while (hi > lo + 1) {
307 size_t mid = (hi + lo) / 2;
308 uint64_t addr_mid = global_variables[mid].addr;
309 if (address < addr_mid) {
310 hi = mid;
311 } else {
312 lo = mid;
313 }
314 }
315
316 if (lo >= global_variables.size()) {
317 return -1;
318 }
319
320 // There may be multiple matching addresses. Walk backwards to find the first one.
321 size_t idx = lo;
322 while (idx > 0 && global_variables[idx - 1].addr == global_variables[lo].addr) {
323 idx--;
324 }
325
326 // Check the address is indeed inside the object found
327 uint64_t end_ptr = global_variables[idx].addr;
328 TypeInfo *t = global_variables[idx].type;
329 if (t == nullptr) {
330 return -1;
331 }
332 uint64_t size = t->size;
333 while (t->type == TypeInfo::Array) {
334 t = t->members[0].type;
335 size *= t->size;
336 }
337 end_ptr += size;
338 if (address < global_variables[idx].addr ||
339 address >= end_ptr) {
340 return -1;
341 }
342
343 return (int)idx;
344 }
345
346 // Get the debug name of a global var from a pointer to it
347 std::string get_global_variable_name(const void *global_pointer, const std::string &type_name = "") {
348 // Find the index of the first global variable with this address
349 int idx = find_global_variable(global_pointer);
350
351 if (idx < 0) {
352 // No matching global variable found.
353 return "";
354 }
355
356 uint64_t address = (uint64_t)global_pointer;
357
358 std::regex re(type_name);
359
360 // Now test all of them
361 for (; (size_t)idx < global_variables.size() && global_variables[idx].addr <= address; idx++) {
362
363 GlobalVariable &v = global_variables[idx];
364 TypeInfo *elem_type = nullptr;
365 if (v.type && v.type->type == TypeInfo::Array && v.type->size) {
366 elem_type = v.type->members[0].type;
367 }
368
369 debug(5) << "Closest global is " << v.name << " at " << std::hex << v.addr << std::dec;
370 if (v.type) {
371 debug(5) << " with type " << v.type->name << "\n";
372 } else {
373 debug(5) << "\n";
374 }
375
376 if (v.addr == address &&
377 (type_name.empty() ||
378 (v.type && regex_match(v.type->name, re)))) {
379 return v.name;
380 } else if (elem_type && // Check if it's an array element
381 (type_name.empty() ||
382 (elem_type && regex_match(elem_type->name, re)))) {
383 int64_t array_size_bytes = v.type->size * elem_type->size;
384 int64_t pos_bytes = address - v.addr;
385 if (pos_bytes >= 0 &&
386 pos_bytes < array_size_bytes &&
387 pos_bytes % elem_type->size == 0) {
388 std::ostringstream oss;
389 oss << v.name << "[" << (pos_bytes / elem_type->size) << "]";
390 debug(5) << "Successful match to array element\n";
391 return oss.str();
392 } else {
393 debug(5) << "Failed match to array element: " << pos_bytes << " " << array_size_bytes << " " << elem_type->size << "\n";
394 }
395 }
396 }
397
398 // No match
399 return "";
400 }

402 void register_heap_object(const void *obj, size_t size, const void *helper) {
403 // helper should be a pointer to a global
404 int idx = find_global_variable(helper);
405 if (idx == -1) {
406 debug(5) << "Could not find helper object: " << helper << "\n";
407 return;
408 }
409 const GlobalVariable &ptr = global_variables[idx];
410 debug(5) << "helper object is " << ptr.name << " at " << std::hex << ptr.addr << std::dec;
411 if (ptr.type) {
412 debug(5) << " with type " << ptr.type->name << "\n";
413 } else {
414 debug(5) << " with unknown type!\n";
415 return;
416 }
417
418 internal_assert(ptr.type->type == TypeInfo::Pointer)
419 << "The type of the helper object was supposed to be a pointer\n";
420 internal_assert(ptr.type->members.size() == 1);
421 TypeInfo *object_type = ptr.type->members[0].type;
422 internal_assert(object_type);
423
424 debug(5) << "The object has type: " << object_type->name << "\n";
425
426 internal_assert(size == object_type->size);
427
428 HeapObject heap_object;
429 heap_object.type = object_type;
430 heap_object.addr = (uint64_t)obj;
431
432 // Recursively enumerate the members.
433 for (size_t i = 0; i < object_type->members.size(); i++) {
434 const LocalVariable &member_spec = object_type->members[i];
435 HeapObject::Member member;
436 member.name = member_spec.name;
437 member.type = member_spec.type;
438 member.addr = heap_object.addr + member_spec.stack_offset;
439 if (member.type) {
440 heap_object.members.push_back(member);
441 debug(5) << member.name << " - " << (int)(member.type->type) << "\n";
442 }
443 }
444
445 // Note that this loop pushes elements onto the vector it's
446 // iterating over as it goes - that's what makes the
447 // enumeration recursive.
448 for (size_t i = 0; i < heap_object.members.size(); i++) {
449 HeapObject::Member parent = heap_object.members[i];
450
451 // Stop at references or pointers. We could register them
452 // recursively (and basically write a garbage collector
453 // object tracker), but that's beyond the scope of what
454 // we're trying to do here. Besides, predicting the
455 // addresses of their children-of-children might follow a
456 // dangling pointer.
457 if (parent.type->type == TypeInfo::Pointer ||
458 parent.type->type == TypeInfo::Reference) {
459 continue;
460 }
461
462 for (size_t j = 0; j < parent.type->members.size(); j++) {
463 const LocalVariable &member_spec = parent.type->members[j];
464 TypeInfo *member_type = member_spec.type;
465
466 HeapObject::Member child;
467 child.type = member_type;
468
469 if (parent.type->type == TypeInfo::Typedef ||
470 parent.type->type == TypeInfo::Const) {
471 // We're just following a type modifier. It's still the same member.
472 child.name = parent.name;
473 } else if (parent.type->type == TypeInfo::Array) {
474 child.name = ""; // the '[index]' gets added in the query routine.
475 } else {
476 child.name = member_spec.name;
477 }
478
479 child.addr = parent.addr + member_spec.stack_offset;
480
481 if (child.type) {
482 debug(5) << child.name << " - " << (int)(child.type->type) << "\n";
483 heap_object.members.push_back(child);
484 }
485 }
486 }
487
488 // Sort by member address, but use stable stort so that parents stay before children.
489 std::stable_sort(heap_object.members.begin(), heap_object.members.end());
490
491 debug(5) << "Children of heap object of type " << object_type->name << " at " << obj << ":\n";
492 for (size_t i = 0; i < heap_object.members.size(); i++) {
493 const HeapObject::Member &mem = heap_object.members[i];
494 debug(5) << std::hex << mem.addr << std::dec << ": " << mem.type->name << " " << mem.name << "\n";
495 }
496
497 heap_objects[heap_object.addr] = heap_object;
498 }
499
500 void deregister_heap_object(const void *obj, size_t size) {
501 heap_objects.erase((uint64_t)obj);
502 }

504 // Get the debug name of a member of a heap variable from a pointer to it
505 std::string get_heap_member_name(const void *ptr, const std::string &type_name = "") {
506 debug(5) << "Getting heap member name of " << ptr << "\n";
507
508 if (heap_objects.empty()) {
509 debug(5) << "No registered heap objects\n";
510 return "";
511 }
512
513 uint64_t addr = (uint64_t)ptr;
514 std::map<uint64_t, HeapObject>::iterator it = heap_objects.upper_bound(addr);
515
516 if (it == heap_objects.begin()) {
517 debug(5) << "No heap objects less than this address\n";
518 return "";
519 }
520
521 // 'it' is the first element strictly greater than addr, so go
522 // back one to get less-than-or-equal-to.
523 it--;
524
525 const HeapObject &obj = it->second;
526 uint64_t object_start = it->first;
527 uint64_t object_end = object_start + obj.type->size;
528 if (addr < object_start || addr >= object_end) {
529 debug(5) << "Not contained in any heap object\n";
530 return "";
531 }
532
533 std::ostringstream name;
534
535 std::regex re(type_name);
536
537 // Look in the members for the appropriate offset.
538 for (size_t i = 0; i < obj.members.size(); i++) {
539 TypeInfo *t = obj.members[i].type;
540
541 if (!t) {
542 continue;
543 }
544
545 debug(5) << "Comparing to member " << obj.members[i].name
546 << " at address " << std::hex << obj.members[i].addr << std::dec
547 << " with type " << t->name
548 << " and type type " << (int)t->type << "\n";
549
550 if (obj.members[i].addr == addr &&
551 (type_name.empty() ||
552 regex_match(t->name, re))) {
553 name << obj.members[i].name;
554 return name.str();
555 }
556
557 // For arrays, we only unpacked the first element.
558 if (t->type == TypeInfo::Array) {
559 TypeInfo *elem_type = t->members[0].type;
560 uint64_t array_start_addr = obj.members[i].addr;
561 uint64_t array_end_addr = array_start_addr + t->size * elem_type->size;
562 debug(5) << "Array runs from " << std::hex << array_start_addr << " to " << array_end_addr << "\n";
563 if (elem_type && addr >= array_start_addr && addr < array_end_addr) {
564 // Adjust the query address backwards to lie
565 // within the first array element and remember the
566 // array index to correct the name later.
567 uint64_t containing_elem = (addr - array_start_addr) / elem_type->size;
568 addr -= containing_elem * elem_type->size;
569 debug(5) << "Query belongs to this array. Adjusting query address backwards to "
570 << std::hex << addr << std::dec << "\n";
571 name << obj.members[i].name << "[" << containing_elem << "]";
572 }
573 } else if (t->type == TypeInfo::Struct ||
574 t->type == TypeInfo::Class ||
575 t->type == TypeInfo::Primitive) {
576 // If I'm not this member, but am contained within it, incorporate its name.
577 uint64_t struct_start_addr = obj.members[i].addr;
578 uint64_t struct_end_addr = struct_start_addr + t->size;
579 debug(5) << "Struct runs from " << std::hex << struct_start_addr << " to " << struct_end_addr << "\n";
580 if (addr >= struct_start_addr && addr < struct_end_addr) {
581 name << obj.members[i].name << ".";
582 }
583 }
584 }
585
586 debug(5) << "Didn't seem to be any of the members of this heap object\n";
587 return "";
588 }

590 // Get the debug name of a stack variable from a pointer to it
591 std::string get_stack_variable_name(const void *stack_pointer, const std::string &type_name = "") {
592
593 // Check it's a plausible stack pointer
594 int marker = 0;
595 uint64_t marker_addr = (uint64_t)&marker;
596 uint64_t top_of_stack;
597 if (marker_addr >> 63) {
598 top_of_stack = (uint64_t)(-1);
599 } else {
600 // Conservatively assume top of stack is first multiple of
601 // 1GB larger than the marker (seriously, who allocates
602 // 1GB of stack space?).
603 top_of_stack = ((marker_addr >> 30) + 1) << 30;
604 }
605
606 if ((uint64_t)stack_pointer > top_of_stack ||
607 (uint64_t)stack_pointer < marker_addr) {
608 return "";
609 }
610
611 struct frame_info {
612 frame_info *frame_pointer;
613 void *return_address;
614 };
615
616 frame_info *fp = (frame_info *)__builtin_frame_address(0);
617 frame_info *next_fp = nullptr;
618
619 // Walk up the stack until we pass the pointer.
620 debug(5) << "Walking up the stack\n";
621 while (fp < stack_pointer) {
622 debug(5) << "frame pointer: " << (void *)(fp->frame_pointer)
623 << " return address: " << fp->return_address << "\n";
624 next_fp = fp;
625 if (fp->frame_pointer < fp) {
626 // If we ever jump downwards, something is
627 // wrong. Maybe this was a heap pointer.
628 debug(5) << "Bailing out because fp decreased\n";
629 return "";
630 }
631 fp = fp->frame_pointer;
632 if (fp < (void *)&marker) {
633 // If we're still below the marker after one hop,
634 // something is wrong. Maybe this was a heap pointer.
635 debug(5) << "Bailing out because we're below the marker\n";
636 return "";
637 }
638 }
639
640 if (!next_fp) {
641 // If we didn't manage to walk up one frame, something is
642 // wrong. Maybe this was a heap pointer.
643 debug(5) << "Bailing out because we didn't even walk up one frame\n";
644 return "";
645 }
646
647 // It's a stack variable in the function containing address
648 // next_fp->return_address
649
650 // Get the program counter at the position of the call
651 uint64_t pc = (uint64_t)(next_fp->return_address) - 5; // -5 for the callq instruction
652
653 FunctionInfo *func = find_containing_function(next_fp->return_address);
654
655 if (!func) {
656 debug(5) << "Bailing out because we couldn't find the containing function\n";
657 return "";
658 }
659
660 // Now what is its offset in that function's frame? The return
661 // address is always at the top of the frame.
662 int offset_above = (int)((int64_t)(stack_pointer) - (int64_t)(fp));
663 int offset_below = (int)((int64_t)(stack_pointer) - (int64_t)(next_fp));
664
665 const int addr_size = sizeof(void *);
666
667 int offset;
668 if (func->frame_base == FunctionInfo::GCC) {
669 offset = offset_above - 2 * addr_size;
670 } else if (func->frame_base == FunctionInfo::ClangFP) {
671 offset = offset_above;
672 } else if (func->frame_base == FunctionInfo::ClangNoFP) {
673 offset = offset_below - 2 * addr_size;
674 } else {
675 debug(5) << "Bailing out because containing function used an unknown mechanism for specifying stack offsets\n";
676 return "";
677 }
678
679 debug(5) << "Searching for var at offset " << offset << "\n";
680
681 std::regex re(type_name);
682
683 for (size_t j = 0; j < func->variables.size(); j++) {
684 const LocalVariable &var = func->variables[j];
685 debug(5) << "Var " << var.name << " is at offset " << var.stack_offset << "\n";
686
687 // Reject it if we're not in its live ranges
688 if (!var.live_ranges.empty()) {
689 bool in_live_range = false;
690 for (size_t i = 0; i < var.live_ranges.size(); i++) {
691 if (pc >= var.live_ranges[i].pc_begin &&
692 pc < var.live_ranges[i].pc_end) {
693 in_live_range = true;
694 break;
695 }
696 }
697 if (!in_live_range) {
698 debug(5) << "Skipping var because we're not in any of its live ranges\n";
699 continue;
700 }
701 }
702
703 TypeInfo *type = var.type;
704 TypeInfo *elem_type = nullptr;
705 if (type && type->type == TypeInfo::Array && type->size) {
706 elem_type = type->members[0].type;
707 }
708
709 if (offset == var.stack_offset && var.type) {
710 debug(5) << "Considering match: " << var.type->name << ", " << var.name << "\n";
711 }
712
713 if (offset == var.stack_offset &&
714 (type_name.empty() ||
715 (type && regex_match(type->name, re)))) {
716 debug(5) << "Successful match to scalar var\n";
717 return var.name;
718 } else if (elem_type && // Check if it's an array element
719 (type_name.empty() ||
720 (elem_type && // Check the type matches
721 regex_match(elem_type->name, re)))) {
722 int64_t array_size_bytes = type->size * elem_type->size;
723 int64_t pos_bytes = offset - var.stack_offset;
724 if (pos_bytes >= 0 &&
725 pos_bytes < array_size_bytes &&
726 pos_bytes % elem_type->size == 0) {
727 std::ostringstream oss;
728 oss << var.name << "[" << (pos_bytes / elem_type->size) << "]";
729 debug(5) << "Successful match to array element\n";
730 return oss.str();
731 } else {
732 debug(5) << "No match to array element: " << type->size << " " << array_size_bytes << " " << pos_bytes << " " << elem_type->size << "\n";
733 }
734 }
735 }
736
737 debug(5) << "Failed to find variable at the matching offset with the given type\n";
738 return "";
739 }
740
741 // Look up n stack frames and get the source location as filename:line
742 std::string get_source_location() {
743 debug(5) << "Finding source location\n";
744
745 if (source_lines.empty()) {
746 debug(5) << "Bailing out because we have no source lines\n";
747 return "";
748 }
749
750 const int max_stack_frames = 256;
751
752 // Get the backtrace
753 vector<void *> trace(max_stack_frames);
754 int trace_size = backtrace(&trace[0], (int)(trace.size()));
755
756 for (int frame = 2; frame < trace_size; frame++) {
757 uint64_t address = (uint64_t)trace[frame];
758
759 debug(5) << "Considering address " << ((void *)address) << "\n";
760
761 // In some situations on OSX (most notable, compiling with different
762 // setting for -fomit-frame-pointer), we can get invalid addresses here that
763 // are small but nonnull (eg, 0x08). It's probably better to miss introspection
764 // options here than to crash during compilation.
765 if (address <= (uint64_t)0xff) {
766 debug(1) << "Bailing out because we found an obviously-bad address in the backtrace. (Did you set -fno-omit-frame-pointer everywhere?)\n";
767 return "";
768 }
769
770 const uint8_t *inst_ptr = (const uint8_t *)address;
771 if (inst_ptr[-5] == 0xe8) {
772 // The actual address of the call is probably 5 bytes
773 // earlier (using callq with an immediate address)
774 address -= 5;
775 } else if (inst_ptr[-2] == 0xff) {
776 // Or maybe it's 2 bytes earlier (using callq with a
777 // register address)
778 address -= 2;
779 } else {
780 debug(5) << "Skipping function because there's no callq before " << (const void *)(inst_ptr) << "\n";
781 continue;
782 }
783
784 // Binary search into functions
785 FunctionInfo *f = find_containing_function((void *)address);
786
787 // If no debug info for this function, we must still be
788 // inside libHalide. Continue searching upwards.
789 if (!f) {
790 debug(5) << "Skipping function because we have no debug info for it\n";
791 continue;
792 }
793
794 debug(5) << "Containing function is " << f->name << "\n";
795
796 // If we're still in the Halide namespace, continue searching
797 if (f->name.size() > 8 &&
798 f->name.substr(0, 8) == "Halide::") {
799 debug(5) << "Skipping function because it's in the Halide namespace\n";
800 continue;
801 }
802
803 // Binary search into source_lines
804 size_t hi = source_lines.size();
805 size_t lo = 0;
806 while (hi > lo + 1) {
807 size_t mid = (hi + lo) / 2;
808 uint64_t pc_mid = source_lines[mid].pc;
809 if (address < pc_mid) {
810 hi = mid;
811 } else {
812 lo = mid;
813 }
814 }
815
816 const std::string &file = source_files[source_lines[lo].file];
817 int line = source_lines[lo].line;
818
819 std::ostringstream oss;
820 oss << file << ":" << line;
821
822 debug(5) << "Source location is " << oss.str() << "\n";
823
824 return oss.str();
825 }
826
827 debug(5) << "Bailing out because we reached the end of the backtrace\n";
828 return "";
829 }
830
831 void dump() {
832 // Dump all the types
833 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); i++) {
834 printf("Class %s of size %llu @ %llx: \n",
835 types[i].name.c_str(),
836 (unsigned long long)(types[i].size),
837 (unsigned long long)(types[i].def_loc));
838 for (size_t j = 0; j < types[i].members.size(); j++) {
839 TypeInfo *c = types[i].members[j].type;
840 const char *type_name = "(unknown)";
841 if (c) {
842 type_name = c->name.c_str();
843 }
844 printf(" Member %s at %d of type %s @ %llx\n",
845 types[i].members[j].name.c_str(),
846 types[i].members[j].stack_offset,
847 type_name,
848 (long long unsigned)types[i].members[j].type_def_loc);
849 }
850 }
851
852 // Dump all the functions and their local variables
853 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
854 const FunctionInfo &f = functions[i];
855 printf("Function %s at %llx - %llx (frame_base %d): \n",
856 f.name.c_str(),
857 (unsigned long long)(f.pc_begin),
858 (unsigned long long)(f.pc_end),
859 (int)f.frame_base);
860 for (size_t j = 0; j < f.variables.size(); j++) {
861 const LocalVariable &v = f.variables[j];
862 TypeInfo *c = v.type;
863 const char *type_name = "(unknown)";
864 if (c) {
865 type_name = c->name.c_str();
866 }
867 printf(" Variable %s at %d of type %s @ %llx\n",
868 v.name.c_str(),
869 v.stack_offset,
870 type_name,
871 (long long unsigned)v.type_def_loc);
872 for (size_t k = 0; k < v.live_ranges.size(); k++) {
873 printf(" Live range: %llx - %llx\n",
874 (unsigned long long)v.live_ranges[k].pc_begin,
875 (unsigned long long)v.live_ranges[k].pc_end);
876 }
877 }
878 }
879
880 // Dump the pc -> source file relationship
881 for (size_t i = 0; i < source_lines.size(); i++) {
882 printf("%p -> %s:%d\n",
883 (void *)(source_lines[i].pc),
884 source_files[source_lines[i].file].c_str(),
885 source_lines[i].line);
886 }
887
888 // Dump the global variables
889 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
890 const GlobalVariable &v = global_variables[i];
891 TypeInfo *c = v.type;
892 const char *type_name = "(unknown)";
893 if (c) {
894 type_name = c->name.c_str();
895 }
896 printf(" Global variable %s at %llx of type %s\n",
897 v.name.c_str(),
898 (long long unsigned)v.addr,
899 type_name);
900 }
901 }
902
903 bool dump_stack_frame(void *ptr) {
904 FunctionInfo *fi = find_containing_function(ptr);
905 if (fi == nullptr) {
906 debug(0) << "Failed to find function containing " << ptr << " in debug info\n";
907 return false;
908 }
909
910 debug(0) << fi->name << ":\n";
911 for (const LocalVariable &v : fi->variables) {
912 TypeInfo *t = v.type;
913 debug(0) << " ";
914 if (t) {
915 debug(0) << t->name << " ";
916 } else {
917 debug(0) << "(unknown type) ";
918 }
919 debug(0) << v.name << " @ " << v.stack_offset << "\n";
920 }
921 return true;
922 }

924private:
925 void load_and_parse_object_file(const std::string &binary) {
926 llvm::object::ObjectFile *obj = nullptr;
927
928 // Open the object file in question.
929 llvm::Expected<llvm::object::OwningBinary<llvm::object::ObjectFile>> maybe_obj =
930 llvm::object::ObjectFile::createObjectFile(binary);
931
932 if (!maybe_obj) {
933 consumeError(maybe_obj.takeError());
934 debug(1) << "Failed to load binary:" << binary << "\n";
935 return;
936 }
937
938 obj = maybe_obj.get().getBinary();
939
940 if (obj) {
941 working = true;
942 parse_object_file(obj);
943 } else {
944 debug(1) << "Could not load object file: " << binary << "\n";
945 working = false;
946 }
947 }
948
949 void parse_object_file(llvm::object::ObjectFile *obj) {
950 // Look for the debug_info, debug_abbrev, debug_line, and debug_str sections
951 llvm::StringRef debug_info, debug_abbrev, debug_str, debug_line, debug_ranges;
952
953#ifdef __APPLE__
954 std::string prefix = "__";
955#else
956 std::string prefix = ".";
957#endif
958
959 for (llvm::object::section_iterator iter = obj->section_begin();
960 iter != obj->section_end(); ++iter) {
961 auto expected_name = iter->getName();
962 internal_assert(expected_name);
963 llvm::StringRef name = expected_name.get();
964 debug(2) << "Section: " << name.str() << "\n";
965 // ignore errors, just leave strings empty
966 auto e = iter->getContents();
967 if (e) {
968 if (name == prefix + "debug_info") {
969 debug_info = *e;
970 } else if (name == prefix + "debug_abbrev") {
971 debug_abbrev = *e;
972 } else if (name == prefix + "debug_str") {
973 debug_str = *e;
974 } else if (name == prefix + "debug_line") {
975 debug_line = *e;
976 } else if (name == prefix + "debug_ranges") {
977 debug_ranges = *e;
978 }
979 }
980 }
981
982 if (debug_info.empty() ||
983 debug_abbrev.empty() ||
984 debug_str.empty() ||
985 debug_line.empty() ||
986 debug_ranges.empty()) {
987 debug(2) << "Debugging sections not found\n";
988 working = false;
989 return;
990 }
991
992 {
993 // Parse the debug_info section to populate the functions and local variables
994 llvm::DataExtractor extractor(debug_info, true, obj->getBytesInAddress());
995 llvm::DataExtractor debug_abbrev_extractor(debug_abbrev, true, obj->getBytesInAddress());
996 parse_debug_info(extractor, debug_abbrev_extractor, debug_str, debug_ranges);
997 }
998
999 {
1000 llvm::DataExtractor e(debug_line, true, obj->getBytesInAddress());
1001 parse_debug_line(e);
1002 }
1003 }
1004
1005 void parse_debug_ranges(const llvm::DataExtractor &e) {
1006 }
1007
1008 void parse_debug_abbrev(const llvm::DataExtractor &e, llvm_offset_t off = 0) {
1009 entry_formats.clear();
1010 while (true) {
1011 EntryFormat fmt;
1012 fmt.code = e.getULEB128(&off);
1013 if (!fmt.code) {
1014 break;
1015 }
1016 fmt.tag = e.getULEB128(&off);
1017 fmt.has_children = (e.getU8(&off) != 0);
1018 // Get the attributes
1019 /*
1020 printf("code = %lu\n"
1021 " tag = %lu\n"
1022 " has_children = %u\n", fmt.code, fmt.tag, fmt.has_children);
1023 */
1024 while (true) {
1025 uint64_t name = e.getULEB128(&off);
1026 uint64_t form = e.getULEB128(&off);
1027 if (!name && !form) {
1028 break;
1029 }
1030 //printf(" name = %lu, form = %lu\n", name, form);
1031
1032 FieldFormat f_fmt(name, form);
1033 fmt.fields.push_back(f_fmt);
1034 }
1035 entry_formats.push_back(fmt);
1036 }
1037 }
1038
1039 void parse_debug_info(const llvm::DataExtractor &e,
1040 const llvm::DataExtractor &debug_abbrev,
1041 llvm::StringRef debug_str,
1042 llvm::StringRef debug_ranges) {
1043 // Offset into the section
1044 llvm_offset_t off = 0;
1045
1046 llvm::StringRef debug_info = e.getData();
1047
1048 // A constant to use indicating that we don't know the stack
1049 // offset of a variable.
1050 const int no_location = 0x80000000;
1051
1052 while (true) {
1053 uint64_t start_of_unit_header = off;
1054
1055 // Parse compilation unit header
1056 bool dwarf_64;
1057 uint64_t unit_length = e.getU32(&off);
1058 if (unit_length == 0xffffffff) {
1059 dwarf_64 = true;
1060 unit_length = e.getU64(&off);
1061 } else {
1062 dwarf_64 = false;
1063 }
1064
1065 if (!unit_length) {
1066 // A zero-length compilation unit indicates the end of
1067 // the list.
1068 break;
1069 }
1070
1071 uint64_t start_of_unit = off;
1072
1073 uint16_t dwarf_version = e.getU16(&off);
1074
1075 uint64_t debug_abbrev_offset = 0;
1076 if (dwarf_64) {
1077 debug_abbrev_offset = e.getU64(&off);
1078 } else {
1079 debug_abbrev_offset = e.getU32(&off);
1080 }
1081 parse_debug_abbrev(debug_abbrev, debug_abbrev_offset);
1082
1083 uint8_t address_size = e.getU8(&off);
1084
1085 vector<pair<FunctionInfo, int>> func_stack;
1086 vector<pair<TypeInfo, int>> type_stack;
1087 vector<pair<std::string, int>> namespace_stack;
1088 vector<pair<vector<LiveRange>, int>> live_range_stack;
1089
1090 int stack_depth = 0;
1091
1092 uint64_t compile_unit_base_pc = 0;
1093
1094 // From the dwarf 4 spec
1095 const unsigned tag_array_type = 0x01;
1096 const unsigned tag_class_type = 0x02;
1097 const unsigned tag_lexical_block = 0x0b;
1098 const unsigned tag_member = 0x0d;
1099 const unsigned tag_pointer_type = 0x0f;
1100 const unsigned tag_reference_type = 0x10;
1101 const unsigned tag_compile_unit = 0x11;
1102 const unsigned tag_structure_type = 0x13;
1103 const unsigned tag_typedef = 0x16;
1104 const unsigned tag_inlined_subroutine = 0x1d;
1105 const unsigned tag_subrange_type = 0x21;
1106 const unsigned tag_base_type = 0x24;
1107 const unsigned tag_const_type = 0x26;
1108 const unsigned tag_function = 0x2e;
1109 const unsigned tag_variable = 0x34;
1110 const unsigned tag_namespace = 0x39;
1111
1112 const unsigned attr_location = 0x02;
1113 const unsigned attr_name = 0x03;
1114 const unsigned attr_byte_size = 0x0b;
1115 const unsigned attr_low_pc = 0x11;
1116 const unsigned attr_high_pc = 0x12;
1117 const unsigned attr_upper_bound = 0x2f;
1118 const unsigned attr_abstract_origin = 0x31;
1119 const unsigned attr_count = 0x37;
1120 const unsigned attr_data_member_location = 0x38;
1121 const unsigned attr_frame_base = 0x40;
1122 const unsigned attr_specification = 0x47;
1123 const unsigned attr_type = 0x49;
1124 const unsigned attr_ranges = 0x55;
1125
1126 while (off - start_of_unit < unit_length) {
1127 uint64_t location = off;
1128
1129 // Grab the next debugging information entry
1130 uint64_t abbrev_code = e.getULEB128(&off);
1131
1132 // A null entry indicates we're popping the stack.
1133 if (abbrev_code == 0) {
1134 if (!func_stack.empty() &&
1135 stack_depth == func_stack.back().second) {
1136 const FunctionInfo &f = func_stack.back().first;
1137 functions.push_back(f);
1138 func_stack.pop_back();
1139 }
1140 if (!type_stack.empty() &&
1141 stack_depth == type_stack.back().second) {
1142 const TypeInfo &c = type_stack.back().first;
1143 types.push_back(c);
1144 type_stack.pop_back();
1145 }
1146 if (!namespace_stack.empty() &&
1147 stack_depth == namespace_stack.back().second) {
1148 namespace_stack.pop_back();
1149 }
1150 if (!live_range_stack.empty() &&
1151 stack_depth == live_range_stack.back().second) {
1152 live_range_stack.pop_back();
1153 }
1154 stack_depth--;
1155 continue;
1156 }
1157
1158 internal_assert(abbrev_code <= entry_formats.size());
1159 const EntryFormat &fmt = entry_formats[abbrev_code - 1];
1160 internal_assert(fmt.code == abbrev_code);
1161
1162 LocalVariable var;
1163 GlobalVariable gvar;
1164 FunctionInfo func;
1165 TypeInfo type_info;
1166 vector<LiveRange> live_ranges;
1167 type_info.def_loc = location;
1168 func.def_loc = location;
1169 var.def_loc = location;
1170 gvar.def_loc = location;
1171 std::string namespace_name;
1172
1173 std::string containing_namespace;
1174 if (!type_stack.empty()) {
1175 containing_namespace = type_stack.back().first.name + "::";
1176 } else {
1177 for (size_t i = 0; i < namespace_stack.size(); i++) {
1178 containing_namespace += namespace_stack[i].first + "::";
1179 }
1180 }
1181
1182 var.stack_offset = no_location;
1183
1184 if (fmt.has_children) {
1185 stack_depth++;
1186 }
1187
1188 // Track local vars found for this function
1189
1190 // Grab the fields
1191 for (size_t i = 0; i < fmt.fields.size(); i++) {
1192 unsigned attr = fmt.fields[i].name;
1193
1194 // A field can either be a constant value:
1195 uint64_t val = 0;
1196 // Or a variable length payload:
1197 const uint8_t *payload = nullptr;
1198 // If payload is non-null, val indicates the
1199 // payload size. If val is zero the payload is a
1200 // null-terminated string.
1201
1202 switch (fmt.fields[i].form) {
1203 case 1: // addr (4 or 8 bytes)
1204 {
1205 if (address_size == 4) {
1206 val = e.getU32(&off);
1207 } else {
1208 val = e.getU64(&off);
1209 }
1210 break;
1211 }
1212 case 2: // There is no case 2
1213 {
1214 internal_error << "What's form 2?";
1215 break;
1216 }
1217 case 3: // block2 (2 byte length followed by payload)
1218 {
1219 val = e.getU16(&off);
1220 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_info.data() + off);
1221 off += val;
1222 break;
1223 }
1224 case 4: // block4 (4 byte length followed by payload)
1225 {
1226 val = e.getU32(&off);
1227 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_info.data() + off);
1228 off += val;
1229 break;
1230 }
1231 case 5: // data2 (2 bytes)
1232 {
1233 val = e.getU16(&off);
1234 break;
1235 }
1236 case 6: // data4 (4 bytes)
1237 {
1238 val = e.getU32(&off);
1239 break;
1240 }
1241 case 7: // data8 (8 bytes)
1242 {
1243 val = e.getU64(&off);
1244 break;
1245 }
1246 case 8: // string (null terminated sequence of bytes)
1247 {
1248 val = 0;
1249 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_info.data() + off);
1250 while (e.getU8(&off)) {
1251 }
1252 break;
1253 }
1254 case 9: // block (uleb128 length followed by payload)
1255 {
1256 val = e.getULEB128(&off);
1257 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_info.data() + off);
1258 off += val;
1259 break;
1260 }
1261 case 10: // block1 (1 byte length followed by payload)
1262 {
1263 val = e.getU8(&off);
1264 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_info.data() + off);
1265 off += val;
1266 break;
1267 }
1268 case 11: // data1 (1 byte)
1269 {
1270 val = e.getU8(&off);
1271 break;
1272 }
1273 case 12: // flag (1 byte)
1274 {
1275 val = e.getU8(&off);
1276 break;
1277 }
1278 case 13: // sdata (sleb128 constant)
1279 {
1280 val = (uint64_t)e.getSLEB128(&off);
1281 break;
1282 }
1283 case 14: // strp (offset into debug_str section. 4 bytes in dwarf 32, 8 in dwarf 64)
1284 {
1285 uint64_t offset;
1286 if (dwarf_64) {
1287 offset = e.getU64(&off);
1288 } else {
1289 offset = e.getU32(&off);
1290 }
1291 val = 0;
1292 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_str.data() + offset);
1293 break;
1294 }
1295 case 15: // udata (uleb128 constant)
1296 {
1297 val = e.getULEB128(&off);
1298 break;
1299 }
1300 case 16: // ref_addr (offset from beginning of debug_info. 4 bytes in dwarf 32, 8 in dwarf 64)
1301 {
1302 if ((dwarf_version <= 2 && address_size == 8) ||
1303 (dwarf_version > 2 && dwarf_64)) {
1304 val = e.getU64(&off);
1305 } else {
1306 val = e.getU32(&off);
1307 }
1308 break;
1309 }
1310 case 17: // ref1 (1 byte offset from the first byte of the compilation unit header)
1311 {
1312 val = e.getU8(&off) + start_of_unit_header;
1313 break;
1314 }
1315 case 18: // ref2 (2 byte version of the same)
1316 {
1317 val = e.getU16(&off) + start_of_unit_header;
1318 break;
1319 }
1320 case 19: // ref4 (4 byte version of the same)
1321 {
1322 val = e.getU32(&off) + start_of_unit_header;
1323 break;
1324 }
1325 case 20: // ref8 (8 byte version of the same)
1326 {
1327 val = e.getU64(&off) + start_of_unit_header;
1328 break;
1329 }
1330 case 21: // ref_udata (uleb128 version of the same)
1331 {
1332 val = e.getULEB128(&off) + start_of_unit_header;
1333 break;
1334 }
1335 case 22: // indirect
1336 {
1337 internal_error << "Can't handle indirect form";
1338 break;
1339 }
1340 case 23: // sec_offset
1341 {
1342 if (dwarf_64) {
1343 val = e.getU64(&off);
1344 } else {
1345 val = e.getU32(&off);
1346 }
1347 break;
1348 }
1349 case 24: // exprloc
1350 {
1351 // Length
1352 val = e.getULEB128(&off);
1353 // Payload (contains a DWARF expression to evaluate (ugh))
1354 payload = (const uint8_t *)(debug_info.data() + off);
1355 off += val;
1356 break;
1357 }
1358 case 25: // flag_present
1359 {
1360 val = 0;
1361 // Just the existence of this field is information apparently? There's no data.
1362 break;
1363 }
1364 case 32: // ref_sig8
1365 {
1366 // 64-bit type signature for a reference in its own type unit
1367 val = e.getU64(&off);
1368 break;
1369 }
1370 default:
1371 internal_error << "Unknown form";
1372 break;
1373 }
1374
1375 if (fmt.tag == tag_function) {
1376 if (attr == attr_name) {
1377 func.name = containing_namespace + std::string((const char *)payload);
1378 } else if (attr == attr_low_pc) {
1379 func.pc_begin = val;
1380 } else if (attr == attr_high_pc) {
1381 if (fmt.fields[i].form == 0x1) {
1382 // Literal address
1383 func.pc_end = val;
1384 } else {
1385 // Size of the thing
1386 func.pc_end = func.pc_begin + val;
1387 }
1388 } else if (attr == attr_frame_base) {
1389 // GCC style
1390 if (val == 1 && payload && payload[0] == 0x9c) {
1391 func.frame_base = FunctionInfo::GCC;
1392 } else if (val == 1 && payload && payload[0] == 0x56 && sizeof(void *) == 8) {
1393 func.frame_base = FunctionInfo::ClangFP;
1394 } else if (val == 1 && payload && payload[0] == 0x55 && sizeof(void *) == 4) {
1395 func.frame_base = FunctionInfo::ClangFP;
1396 } else if (val == 1 && payload && payload[0] == 0x57 && sizeof(void *) == 8) {
1397 func.frame_base = FunctionInfo::ClangNoFP;
1398 } else if (val == 1 && payload && payload[0] == 0x54 && sizeof(void *) == 4) {
1399 func.frame_base = FunctionInfo::ClangNoFP;
1400 } else {
1401 func.frame_base = FunctionInfo::Unknown;
1402 }
1403 } else if (attr == attr_specification) {
1404 func.spec_loc = val;
1405 }
1406 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_base_type) {
1407 if (attr == attr_name) {
1408 type_info.name = containing_namespace + std::string((const char *)payload);
1409 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Primitive;
1410 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1411 type_info.size = val;
1412 }
1413 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_class_type) {
1414 if (attr == attr_name) {
1415 type_info.name = containing_namespace + std::string((const char *)payload);
1416 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Class;
1417 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1418 type_info.size = val;
1419 }
1420 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_structure_type) {
1421 if (attr == attr_name) {
1422 type_info.name = containing_namespace + std::string((const char *)payload);
1423 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Struct;
1424 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1425 type_info.size = val;
1426 }
1427 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_typedef) {
1428 if (attr == attr_name) {
1429 type_info.name = containing_namespace + std::string((const char *)payload);
1430 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Typedef;
1431 } else if (attr == attr_type) {
1432 // Approximate a typedef as a single-member class
1433 LocalVariable m;
1434 m.type_def_loc = val;
1435 m.stack_offset = 0;
1436 type_info.members.push_back(m);
1437 }
1438 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_pointer_type) {
1439 if (attr == attr_type) {
1440 // Approximate a pointer type as a single-member class
1441 LocalVariable m;
1442 m.type_def_loc = val;
1443 m.stack_offset = 0;
1444 type_info.members.push_back(m);
1445 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Pointer;
1446 // Assume the size is the address size
1447 type_info.size = address_size;
1448 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1449 // Should really be 4 or 8
1450 type_info.size = val;
1451 }
1452 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_reference_type) {
1453 if (attr == attr_type) {
1454 LocalVariable m;
1455 m.type_def_loc = val;
1456 m.stack_offset = 0;
1457 type_info.members.push_back(m);
1458 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Reference;
1459 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1460 // Should really be 4 or 8
1461 type_info.size = val;
1462 }
1463 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_const_type) {
1464 if (attr == attr_type) {
1465 LocalVariable m;
1466 m.type_def_loc = val;
1467 m.stack_offset = 0;
1468 type_info.members.push_back(m);
1469 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Const;
1470 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1471 // Should really be 4 or 8
1472 type_info.size = val;
1473 }
1474 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_array_type) {
1475 if (attr == attr_type) {
1476 LocalVariable m;
1477 m.type_def_loc = val;
1478 m.stack_offset = 0;
1479 type_info.members.push_back(m);
1480 type_info.type = TypeInfo::Array;
1481 } else if (attr == attr_byte_size) {
1482 // According to the dwarf spec, this
1483 // should be the number of bytes the array
1484 // occupies, but compilers seem to emit
1485 // the number of array entries instead.
1486 type_info.size = val;
1487 }
1488 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_variable) {
1489 if (attr == attr_name) {
1490 if (func_stack.empty()) {
1491 // Global var
1492 gvar.name = containing_namespace + std::string((const char *)payload);
1493 } else {
1494 // Either a local var, or a static var inside a function
1495 gvar.name = var.name = std::string((const char *)payload);
1496 }
1497 } else if (attr == attr_location) {
1498 // We only understand locations which are
1499 // offsets from the function's frame
1500 if (payload && payload[0] == 0x91) {
1501 // It's a local
1502 // payload + 1 is a sleb128
1503 var.stack_offset = (int)(get_sleb128(payload + 1));
1504 } else if (payload && payload[0] == 0x03 && val == (sizeof(void *) + 1)) {
1505 // It's a global
1506 // payload + 1 is an address
1507 const void *addr = load_misaligned((const void *const *)(payload + 1));
1508 gvar.addr = (uint64_t)(addr);
1509 } else {
1510 // Some other format that we don't understand
1511 var.stack_offset = no_location;
1512 }
1513 } else if (attr == attr_type) {
1514 var.type_def_loc = val;
1515 gvar.type_def_loc = val;
1516 } else if (attr == attr_abstract_origin) {
1517 // This is a stack variable imported from a function that was inlined.
1518 var.origin_loc = val;
1519 } else if (attr == attr_specification) {
1520 // This is an instance of a global var with a prototype elsewhere
1521 gvar.spec_loc = val;
1522 }
1523 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_member) {
1524 if (attr == attr_name) {
1525 var.name = std::string((const char *)payload);
1526 if (!type_stack.empty()) {
1527 gvar.name = type_stack.back().first.name + "::" + var.name;
1528 } else {
1529 gvar.name = var.name;
1530 }
1531 } else if (attr == attr_data_member_location) {
1532 if (!payload) {
1533 var.stack_offset = val;
1534 } else if (payload[0] == 0x23) {
1535 var.stack_offset = (int)(get_uleb128(payload + 1));
1536 }
1537 } else if (attr == attr_type) {
1538 var.type_def_loc = val;
1539 gvar.type_def_loc = val;
1540 }
1541 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_namespace) {
1542 if (attr == attr_name) {
1543 namespace_name = std::string((const char *)payload);
1544 }
1545 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_subrange_type) {
1546 // Could be telling us the size of an array type
1547 if (attr == attr_upper_bound &&
1548 !type_stack.empty() &&
1549 type_stack.back().first.type == TypeInfo::Array) {
1550 type_stack.back().first.size = val + 1;
1551 } else if (attr == attr_count &&
1552 !type_stack.empty() &&
1553 type_stack.back().first.type == TypeInfo::Array) {
1554 type_stack.back().first.size = val;
1555 }
1556 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_inlined_subroutine ||
1557 fmt.tag == tag_lexical_block) {
1558 if (attr == attr_low_pc) {
1559 LiveRange r = {val, val};
1560 live_ranges.push_back(r);
1561 } else if (attr == attr_high_pc && !live_ranges.empty()) {
1562 if (fmt.fields[i].form == 0x1) {
1563 // Literal address
1564 live_ranges.back().pc_end = val;
1565 } else {
1566 // Size
1567 live_ranges.back().pc_end = live_ranges.back().pc_begin + val;
1568 }
1569 } else if (attr == attr_ranges) {
1570 if (val < debug_ranges.size()) {
1571 // It's an array of addresses
1572 const void *const *ptr = (const void *const *)(debug_ranges.data() + val);
1573 const void *const *end = (const void *const *)(debug_ranges.data() + debug_ranges.size());
1574 // Note: might not be properly aligned; use memcpy to avoid
1575 // sanitizer warnings
1576 while (load_misaligned(ptr) && ptr < end - 1) {
1577 LiveRange r = {(uint64_t)load_misaligned(ptr), (uint64_t)load_misaligned(ptr + 1)};
1578 r.pc_begin += compile_unit_base_pc;
1579 r.pc_end += compile_unit_base_pc;
1580 live_ranges.push_back(r);
1581 ptr += 2;
1582 }
1583 }
1584 }
1585 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_compile_unit) {
1586 if (attr == attr_low_pc) {
1587 compile_unit_base_pc = val;
1588 }
1589 }
1590 }
1591
1592 if (fmt.tag == tag_variable) {
1593 if (!func_stack.empty() && !gvar.addr) {
1594 if (!live_range_stack.empty()) {
1595 var.live_ranges = live_range_stack.back().first;
1596 }
1597 func_stack.back().first.variables.push_back(var);
1598 } else {
1599 global_variables.push_back(gvar);
1600 }
1601 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_member &&
1602 !type_stack.empty()) {
1603 if (var.stack_offset == no_location) {
1604 // A member with no stack offset location is probably the prototype for a static member
1605 global_variables.push_back(gvar);
1606 } else {
1607 type_stack.back().first.members.push_back(var);
1608 }
1609
1610 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_function) {
1611 if (fmt.has_children) {
1612 func_stack.emplace_back(func, stack_depth);
1613 } else {
1614 functions.push_back(func);
1615 }
1616 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_class_type ||
1617 fmt.tag == tag_structure_type ||
1618 fmt.tag == tag_array_type ||
1619 fmt.tag == tag_base_type) {
1620 if (fmt.has_children) {
1621 type_stack.emplace_back(type_info, stack_depth);
1622 } else {
1623 types.push_back(type_info);
1624 }
1625 } else if ((fmt.tag == tag_typedef ||
1626 fmt.tag == tag_pointer_type ||
1627 fmt.tag == tag_reference_type ||
1628 fmt.tag == tag_const_type) &&
1629 type_info.members.size() == 1) {
1630 types.push_back(type_info);
1631 } else if (fmt.tag == tag_namespace && fmt.has_children) {
1632 if (namespace_name.empty()) {
1633 namespace_name = "_";
1634 }
1635 namespace_stack.emplace_back(namespace_name, stack_depth);
1636 } else if ((fmt.tag == tag_inlined_subroutine ||
1637 fmt.tag == tag_lexical_block) &&
1638 !live_ranges.empty() && fmt.has_children) {
1639 live_range_stack.emplace_back(live_ranges, stack_depth);
1640 }
1641 }
1642 }
1643
1644 // Connect function definitions to their declarations
1645 {
1646 std::map<uint64_t, FunctionInfo *> func_map;
1647 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1648 func_map[functions[i].def_loc] = &functions[i];
1649 }
1650
1651 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1652 if (functions[i].spec_loc) {
1653 FunctionInfo *spec = func_map[functions[i].spec_loc];
1654 if (spec) {
1655 functions[i].name = spec->name;
1656 }
1657 }
1658 }
1659 }
1660
1661 // Connect inlined variable instances to their origins
1662 {
1663 std::map<uint64_t, LocalVariable *> var_map;
1664 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1665 for (size_t j = 0; j < functions[i].variables.size(); j++) {
1666 var_map[functions[i].variables[j].def_loc] = &(functions[i].variables[j]);
1667 }
1668 }
1669
1670 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1671 for (size_t j = 0; j < functions[i].variables.size(); j++) {
1672 LocalVariable &v = functions[i].variables[j];
1673 uint64_t loc = v.origin_loc;
1674 if (loc) {
1675 LocalVariable *origin = var_map[loc];
1676 if (origin) {
1677 v.name = origin->name;
1678 v.type = origin->type;
1679 v.type_def_loc = origin->type_def_loc;
1680 } else {
1681 debug(5) << "Variable with bad abstract origin: " << loc << "\n";
1682 }
1683 }
1684 }
1685 }
1686 }
1687
1688 // Connect global variable instances to their prototypes
1689 {
1690 std::map<uint64_t, GlobalVariable *> var_map;
1691 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
1692 GlobalVariable &var = global_variables[i];
1693 debug(5) << "var " << var.name << " is at " << var.def_loc << "\n";
1694 if (var.spec_loc || var.name.empty()) {
1695 // Not a prototype
1696 continue;
1697 }
1698 var_map[var.def_loc] = &var;
1699 }
1700
1701 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
1702 GlobalVariable &var = global_variables[i];
1703 if (var.name.empty() && var.spec_loc) {
1704 GlobalVariable *spec = var_map[var.spec_loc];
1705 if (spec) {
1706 var.name = spec->name;
1707 var.type = spec->type;
1708 var.type_def_loc = spec->type_def_loc;
1709 } else {
1710 debug(5) << "Global variable with bad spec loc: " << var.spec_loc << "\n";
1711 }
1712 }
1713 }
1714 }
1715
1716 // Hook up the type pointers
1717 {
1718 std::map<uint64_t, TypeInfo *> type_map;
1719 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); i++) {
1720 type_map[types[i].def_loc] = &types[i];
1721 }
1722
1723 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1724 for (size_t j = 0; j < functions[i].variables.size(); j++) {
1725 functions[i].variables[j].type =
1726 type_map[functions[i].variables[j].type_def_loc];
1727 }
1728 }
1729
1730 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
1731 global_variables[i].type =
1732 type_map[global_variables[i].type_def_loc];
1733 }
1734
1735 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); i++) {
1736 for (size_t j = 0; j < types[i].members.size(); j++) {
1737 types[i].members[j].type =
1738 type_map[types[i].members[j].type_def_loc];
1739 }
1740 }
1741 }
1742
1743 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); i++) {
1744 // Set the names of the pointer types
1745 vector<std::string> suffix;
1746 TypeInfo *t = &types[i];
1747 while (t) {
1748 if (t->type == TypeInfo::Pointer) {
1749 suffix.emplace_back("*");
1750 internal_assert(t->members.size() == 1);
1751 t = t->members[0].type;
1752 } else if (t->type == TypeInfo::Reference) {
1753 suffix.emplace_back("&");
1754 internal_assert(t->members.size() == 1);
1755 t = t->members[0].type;
1756 } else if (t->type == TypeInfo::Const) {
1757 suffix.emplace_back("const");
1758 internal_assert(t->members.size() == 1);
1759 t = t->members[0].type;
1760 } else if (t->type == TypeInfo::Array) {
1761 // Do we know the size?
1762 if (t->size != 0) {
1763 std::ostringstream oss;
1764 oss << "[" << t->size << "]";
1765 suffix.push_back(oss.str());
1766 } else {
1767 suffix.emplace_back("[]");
1768 }
1769 internal_assert(t->members.size() == 1);
1770 t = t->members[0].type;
1771 } else {
1772 break;
1773 }
1774 }
1775
1776 if (t && !suffix.empty()) {
1777 types[i].name = t->name;
1778 while (!suffix.empty()) {
1779 types[i].name += " " + suffix.back();
1780 suffix.pop_back();
1781 }
1782 }
1783 }
1784
1785 // Fix up the sizes of typedefs where we know the underlying type
1786 for (size_t i = 0; i < types.size(); i++) {
1787 TypeInfo *t = &types[i];
1788 if (types[i].type == TypeInfo::Typedef &&
1789 !t->members.empty() &&
1790 t->members[0].type) {
1791 t->size = t->members[0].type->size;
1792 }
1793 }
1794
1795 // Unpack class members into the local variables list.
1796 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1797 vector<LocalVariable> new_vars = functions[i].variables;
1798 for (size_t j = 0; j < new_vars.size(); j++) {
1799 // If new_vars[j] is a class type, unpack its members
1800 // immediately after this point.
1801 const LocalVariable &v = new_vars[j];
1802 if (v.type &&
1803 (v.type->type == TypeInfo::Struct ||
1804 v.type->type == TypeInfo::Class ||
1805 v.type->type == TypeInfo::Typedef)) {
1806 size_t members = v.type->members.size();
1807 new_vars.insert(new_vars.begin() + j + 1,
1808 v.type->members.begin(),
1809 v.type->members.end());
1810
1811 // Typedefs retain the same name and stack offset
1812 if (new_vars[j].type->type == TypeInfo::Typedef) {
1813 new_vars[j + 1].name = new_vars[j].name;
1814 new_vars[j + 1].stack_offset = new_vars[j].stack_offset;
1815 } else {
1816 // Correct the stack offsets and names
1817 for (size_t k = 0; k < members; k++) {
1818 new_vars[j + k + 1].stack_offset += new_vars[j].stack_offset;
1819 if (!new_vars[j + k + 1].name.empty() &&
1820 !new_vars[j].name.empty()) {
1821 new_vars[j + k + 1].name = new_vars[j].name + "." + new_vars[j + k + 1].name;
1822 }
1823 }
1824 }
1825 }
1826 }
1827 functions[i].variables.swap(new_vars);
1828
1829 if (!functions[i].variables.empty()) {
1830 debug(5) << "Function " << functions[i].name << ":\n";
1831 for (size_t j = 0; j < functions[i].variables.size(); j++) {
1832 if (functions[i].variables[j].type) {
1833 debug(5) << " " << functions[i].variables[j].type->name << " " << functions[i].variables[j].name << "\n";
1834 }
1835 }
1836 }
1837 }
1838
1839 // Unpack class members of global variables
1840 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
1841 GlobalVariable v = global_variables[i];
1842 if (v.type && v.addr &&
1843 (v.type->type == TypeInfo::Struct ||
1844 v.type->type == TypeInfo::Class ||
1845 v.type->type == TypeInfo::Typedef)) {
1846 debug(5) << "Unpacking members of " << v.name << " at " << std::hex << v.addr << "\n";
1847 vector<LocalVariable> &members = v.type->members;
1848 for (size_t j = 0; j < members.size(); j++) {
1849 GlobalVariable mem;
1850 if (!v.name.empty() && !members[j].name.empty()) {
1851 mem.name = v.name + "." + members[j].name;
1852 } else {
1853 // Might be a member of an anonymous struct?
1854 mem.name = members[j].name;
1855 }
1856 mem.type = members[j].type;
1857 mem.type_def_loc = members[j].type_def_loc;
1858 mem.addr = v.addr + members[j].stack_offset;
1859 debug(5) << " Member " << mem.name << " goes at " << mem.addr << "\n";
1860 global_variables.push_back(mem);
1861 }
1862 debug(5) << std::dec;
1863 }
1864 }
1865
1866 // Drop functions for which we don't know the program counter,
1867 // and variables for which we don't know the stack offset,
1868 // name, or type.
1869 {
1870 vector<FunctionInfo> trimmed;
1871 for (size_t i = 0; i < functions.size(); i++) {
1872 FunctionInfo &f = functions[i];
1873 if (!f.pc_begin ||
1874 !f.pc_end ||
1875 f.name.empty()) {
1876 //debug(5) << "Dropping " << f.name << "\n";
1877 continue;
1878 }
1879
1880 vector<LocalVariable> vars;
1881 for (size_t j = 0; j < f.variables.size(); j++) {
1882 LocalVariable &v = f.variables[j];
1883 if (!v.name.empty() && v.type && v.stack_offset != no_location) {
1884 vars.push_back(v);
1885 } else {
1886 //debug(5) << "Dropping " << v.name << "\n";
1887 }
1888 }
1889 f.variables.clear();
1890 trimmed.push_back(f);
1891 trimmed.back().variables = vars;
1892 }
1893 std::swap(functions, trimmed);
1894 }
1895
1896 // Drop globals for which we don't know the address or name
1897 {
1898 vector<GlobalVariable> trimmed;
1899 for (size_t i = 0; i < global_variables.size(); i++) {
1900 GlobalVariable &v = global_variables[i];
1901 if (!v.name.empty() && v.addr) {
1902 trimmed.push_back(v);
1903 }
1904 }
1905
1906 std::swap(global_variables, trimmed);
1907 }
1908
1909 // Sort the functions list by program counter
1910 std::sort(functions.begin(), functions.end());
1911
1912 // Sort the global variables by address
1913 std::sort(global_variables.begin(), global_variables.end());
1914 }
1915
1916 void parse_debug_line(const llvm::DataExtractor &e) {
1917 llvm_offset_t off = 0;
1918
1919 // For every compilation unit
1920 while (true) {
1921 // Parse the header
1922 uint32_t unit_length = e.getU32(&off);
1923
1924 if (unit_length == 0) {
1925 // No more units
1926 break;
1927 }
1928
1929 llvm_offset_t unit_end = off + unit_length;
1930
1931 debug(5) << "Parsing compilation unit from " << off << " to " << unit_end << "\n";
1932
1933 uint16_t version = e.getU16(&off);
1934 internal_assert(version >= 2);
1935
1936 uint32_t header_length = e.getU32(&off);
1937 llvm_offset_t end_header_off = off + header_length;
1938 uint8_t min_instruction_length = e.getU8(&off);
1939 uint8_t max_ops_per_instruction = 1;
1940 if (version >= 4) {
1941 // This is for VLIW architectures
1942 max_ops_per_instruction = e.getU8(&off);
1943 }
1944 uint8_t default_is_stmt = e.getU8(&off);
1945 int8_t line_base = (int8_t)e.getU8(&off);
1946 uint8_t line_range = e.getU8(&off);
1947 uint8_t opcode_base = e.getU8(&off);
1948
1949 vector<uint8_t> standard_opcode_length(opcode_base);
1950 for (int i = 1; i < opcode_base; i++) {
1951 // Note we don't use entry 0
1952 standard_opcode_length[i] = e.getU8(&off);
1953 }
1954
1955 vector<std::string> include_dirs;
1956 // The current directory is implicitly the first dir.
1957 include_dirs.emplace_back(".");
1958 while (off < end_header_off) {
1959 const char *s = e.getCStr(&off);
1960 if (s && s[0]) {
1961 include_dirs.emplace_back(s);
1962 } else {
1963 break;
1964 }
1965 }
1966
1967 // The first source file index for this compilation unit.
1968 int source_files_base = source_files.size();
1969
1970 while (off < end_header_off) {
1971 const char *name = e.getCStr(&off);
1972 if (name && name[0]) {
1973 uint64_t dir = e.getULEB128(&off);
1974 uint64_t mod_time = e.getULEB128(&off);
1975 uint64_t length = e.getULEB128(&off);
1976 (void)mod_time;
1977 (void)length;
1978 internal_assert(dir <= include_dirs.size());
1979 source_files.push_back(include_dirs[dir] + "/" + name);
1980 } else {
1981 break;
1982 }
1983 }
1984
1985 internal_assert(off == end_header_off) << "Failed parsing section .debug_line";
1986
1987 // Now parse the table. It uses a state machine with the following fields:
1988 struct {
1989 // Current program counter
1990 uint64_t address;
1991 // Which op within that instruction (for VLIW archs)
1992 uint32_t op_index;
1993 // File and line index;
1994 uint32_t file, line, column;
1995 bool is_stmt, basic_block, end_sequence, prologue_end, epilogue_begin;
1996 // The ISA of the architecture (e.g. x86-64 vs armv7 vs thumb)
1997 uint32_t isa;
1998 // The id of the block to which this line belongs
1999 uint32_t discriminator;
2000
2001 void append_row(vector<LineInfo> &lines) {
2002 LineInfo l = {address, line, file};
2003 lines.push_back(l);
2004 }
2005 } state, initial_state;
2006
2007 // Initialize the state table.
2008 initial_state.address = 0;
2009 initial_state.op_index = 0;
2010 initial_state.file = 0;
2011 initial_state.line = 1;
2012 initial_state.column = 0;
2013 initial_state.is_stmt = default_is_stmt;
2014 initial_state.basic_block = false;
2015 initial_state.end_sequence = false;
2016 initial_state.prologue_end = false;
2017 initial_state.epilogue_begin = false;
2018 initial_state.isa = 0;
2019 initial_state.discriminator = 0;
2020 state = initial_state;
2021
2022 // For every sequence.
2023 while (off < unit_end) {
2024 uint8_t opcode = e.getU8(&off);
2025
2026 if (opcode == 0) {
2027 // Extended opcodes
2028 llvm_offset_t ext_offset = off;
2029 uint64_t len = e.getULEB128(&off);
2030 llvm_offset_t arg_size = len - (off - ext_offset);
2031 uint8_t sub_opcode = e.getU8(&off);
2032 switch (sub_opcode) {
2033 case 1: // end_sequence
2034 {
2035 state.end_sequence = true;
2036 state.append_row(source_lines);
2037 state = initial_state;
2038 break;
2039 }
2040 case 2: // set_address
2041 {
2042 state.address = e.getAddress(&off);
2043 break;
2044 }
2045 case 3: // define_file
2046 {
2047 const char *name = e.getCStr(&off);
2048 uint64_t dir_index = e.getULEB128(&off);
2049 uint64_t mod_time = e.getULEB128(&off);
2050 uint64_t length = e.getULEB128(&off);
2051 (void)mod_time;
2052 (void)length;
2053 internal_assert(dir_index < include_dirs.size());
2054 source_files.push_back(include_dirs[dir_index] + "/" + name);
2055 break;
2056 }
2057 case 4: // set_discriminator
2058 {
2059 state.discriminator = e.getULEB128(&off);
2060 break;
2061 }
2062 default: // Some unknown thing. Skip it.
2063 off += arg_size;
2064 }
2065 } else if (opcode < opcode_base) {
2066 // A standard opcode
2067 switch (opcode) {
2068 case 1: // copy
2069 {
2070 state.append_row(source_lines);
2071 state.basic_block = false;
2072 state.prologue_end = false;
2073 state.epilogue_begin = false;
2074 state.discriminator = 0;
2075 break;
2076 }
2077 case 2: // advance_pc
2078 {
2079 uint64_t advance = e.getULEB128(&off);
2080 state.address += min_instruction_length * ((state.op_index + advance) / max_ops_per_instruction);
2081 state.op_index = (state.op_index + advance) % max_ops_per_instruction;
2082 break;
2083 }
2084 case 3: // advance_line
2085 {
2086 state.line += e.getSLEB128(&off);
2087 break;
2088 }
2089 case 4: // set_file
2090 {
2091 state.file = e.getULEB128(&off) - 1 + source_files_base;
2092 break;
2093 }
2094 case 5: // set_column
2095 {
2096 state.column = e.getULEB128(&off);
2097 break;
2098 }
2099 case 6: // negate_stmt
2100 {
2101 state.is_stmt = !state.is_stmt;
2102 break;
2103 }
2104 case 7: // set_basic_block
2105 {
2106 state.basic_block = true;
2107 break;
2108 }
2109 case 8: // const_add_pc
2110 {
2111 // Same as special opcode 255 (but doesn't emit a row or reset state)
2112 uint8_t adjust_opcode = 255 - opcode_base;
2113 uint64_t advance = adjust_opcode / line_range;
2114 state.address += min_instruction_length * ((state.op_index + advance) / max_ops_per_instruction);
2115 state.op_index = (state.op_index + advance) % max_ops_per_instruction;
2116 break;
2117 }
2118 case 9: // fixed_advance_pc
2119 {
2120 uint16_t advance = e.getU16(&off);
2121 state.address += advance;
2122 break;
2123 }
2124 case 10: // set_prologue_end
2125 {
2126 state.prologue_end = true;
2127 break;
2128 }
2129 case 11: // set_epilogue_begin
2130 {
2131 state.epilogue_begin = true;
2132 break;
2133 }
2134 case 12: // set_isa
2135 {
2136 state.isa = e.getULEB128(&off);
2137 break;
2138 }
2139 default: {
2140 // Unknown standard opcode. Skip over the args.
2141 uint8_t args = standard_opcode_length[opcode];
2142 for (int i = 0; i < args; i++) {
2143 e.getULEB128(&off);
2144 }
2145 }
2146 }
2147 } else {
2148 // Special opcode
2149 uint8_t adjust_opcode = opcode - opcode_base;
2150 uint64_t advance_op = adjust_opcode / line_range;
2151 uint64_t advance_line = line_base + adjust_opcode % line_range;
2152 state.address += min_instruction_length * ((state.op_index + advance_op) / max_ops_per_instruction);
2153 state.op_index = (state.op_index + advance_op) % max_ops_per_instruction;
2154 state.line += advance_line;
2155 state.append_row(source_lines);
2156 state.basic_block = false;
2157 state.prologue_end = false;
2158 state.epilogue_begin = false;
2159 state.discriminator = 0;
2160 }
2161 }
2162 }
2163
2164 // Sort the sequences and functions by low PC to make searching into it faster.
2165 std::sort(source_lines.begin(), source_lines.end());
2166 }
2167
2168 FunctionInfo *find_containing_function(void *addr) {
2169 uint64_t address = (uint64_t)addr;
2170 debug(5) << "Searching for function containing address " << addr << "\n";
2171 size_t hi = functions.size();
2172 size_t lo = 0;
2173 while (hi > lo) {
2174 size_t mid = (hi + lo) / 2;
2175 uint64_t pc_mid_begin = functions[mid].pc_begin;
2176 uint64_t pc_mid_end = functions[mid].pc_end;
2177 if (address < pc_mid_begin) {
2178 hi = mid;
2179 } else if (address > pc_mid_end) {
2180 lo = mid + 1;
2181 } else {
2182 debug(5) << "At function " << functions[mid].name
2183 << " spanning: " << (void *)pc_mid_begin
2184 << ", " << (void *)pc_mid_end << "\n";
2185 return &functions[mid];
2186 }
2187 }
2188
2189 return nullptr;
2190 }
2191
2192 int64_t get_sleb128(const uint8_t *ptr) {
2193 int64_t result = 0;
2194 unsigned shift = 0;
2195 uint8_t byte = 0;
2196
2197 while (true) {
2198 internal_assert(shift < 57);
2199 byte = *ptr++;
2200 result |= (uint64_t)(byte & 0x7f) << shift;
2201 shift += 7;
2202 if ((byte & 0x80) == 0) {
2203 break;
2204 }
2205 }
2206
2207 // Second-highest bit of the final byte gives the sign.
2208 if (shift < 64 && (byte & 0x40)) {
2209 // Fill the rest of the bytes with ones.
2210 result |= -(1ULL << shift);
2211 }
2212
2213 return result;
2214 }
2215
2216 int64_t get_uleb128(const uint8_t *ptr) {
2217 uint64_t result = 0;
2218 unsigned shift = 0;
2219 uint8_t byte = 0;
2220
2221 while (true) {
2222 internal_assert(shift < 57);
2223 byte = *ptr++;
2224 result |= (uint64_t)(byte & 0x7f) << shift;
2225 shift += 7;
2226 if ((byte & 0x80) == 0) {
2227 return result;
2228 }
2229 }
2230 }
2231};

2288bool saves_frame_pointer(void *fn) {
2289 // On x86-64, if we save the frame pointer, the first two instructions should be pushing the stack pointer and the frame pointer:
2290 const uint8_t *ptr = (const uint8_t *)(fn);
2291 // Skip over a valid-branch-target marker (endbr64), if there is
2292 // one. These sometimes start functions to help detect control flow
2293 // violations.
2294 if (ptr[0] == 0xf3 && ptr[1] == 0x0f && ptr[2] == 0x1e && ptr[3] == 0xfa) {
2295 ptr += 4;
2296 }
2297 return ptr[0] == 0x55; // push %rbp
2298}
